   <documentation>
      <row>
         <Docu><![CDATA[= Action name =
PCK.AUTOMIC_JSON.PUB.ACTION.ADD_UPDATE_JSON_CONTENT

= General description =
This action adds/updates the content of the specific object in JSON format.

= Inputs =
- JSON File Path: 	Provide full path to the JSON file. E.g. C:\json.txt
- JSON Content: 	Provide JSON or an AE Variable that contains JSON content. E.g. &JSON#
- JSON Path*: 		Provide the path to the JSON element to add the block into it or update E.g. Dev.Server[0]
- Key: 			Provide key to the JSON element to add or update the block into it. Required while adding a new key-value pair. E.g. IP
- Value Type: 		Specify if value to be added is of type String or Other object.
- Value: 		Provide the value to be added/updated to specified JSON path. E.g. { "IP" : "127.0.0.1" }
- Overwrite: 		Specify whether to update the value if path/key already exists.
- Download Path:	Specify path to download modified file. E.g. D:\Json\filename.json

Note: JSON File Path and JSON Content are mutually exclusive.
	
= Failure Condition=
1) IfÃÂÃÂÃÂÃÂtheÃÂÃÂÃÂÃÂspecified JSONÃÂÃÂÃÂÃÂpath does not exist..
2) If the specified JSON variables does not contain JSON Content. 

= Behavior =
- If path/key already exist and 'Overwrite' is set to NO, JSON will not be updated.
- If the value to be added/updated as of string type, pass the 'Value Type' as String.For all Others, pass it as Others.
- If Key does not exist at specified Path, it will be created with the provided Value.
- ÃÂÃÂÃÂÃÂIf the value entered inÃÂÃÂÃÂÃÂDownload Path is notÃÂÃÂÃÂÃÂan absoluteÃÂÃÂÃÂÃÂpath, the modified file is downloaded to the agent directory.
- The downloaded file will get overwritten if it already exists.

=Return Value=
UC4RB_JSN_UPDATED_JSON# : Updated JSON

= Outputs =
* Return code is 0 in case of success.
* Return code is non-zero in case of failure.

= Rollback =
(none)

= Logging =
AE logs will be displayed in the AE report.

]]></Docu>
